User module:
  
* Departments
  1. id
  2. name
  3. created_at
  4. updated_at

* Users:
  1. id
  2. name
  3. email
  4. password
  5. phone
  6. empUserId (auto generate)
  7. date of birth
  8. address
  9. status
 10. department_id
 12. created_at
 13. updated_at

* user_salary_informations:

  1. id
  2. name
  3. Basic
  4. House Rent Allowance
  5. Car Allowance/Conveyance 
  6. Medical Allowance
  7. Special Allowances
  8. Festival Bonus
  9. Incentive Bonus
 10. Arrear Others
 11. empUserId
 12. created_at
 13. updated_at
 
  
* roles:
  1. id
  2. name       (accountant)
  3. role_id    (auto generated)
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at

  
* permission_lists (static):
  1. id
  2. permission_name
  3. permission_id  (auto generated)
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  

* role_permissions:
  1. id
  2. role_id
  3. permission_id
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  
* user_roles:
  1. id
  2. role_id
  3. user_id
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  
  
* forgot_password_logs:
  1. id
  2. request_header
  3. request_time
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  
* Steps:
  1. user full information management by admin            -> CRUD
  2. Departments management by admin                      -> CRUD
  3. user_salary_informations  management by admin        -> CRUD
  4. roles management by admin                            -> CRUD
  5. role_permissions set by admin                        -> CRUD
  6. user_roles assign by admin                           -> CRUD
  7. login
  8. forget_passwords management
  9. forgot_password_logs management management by admin  
 10. view user profile with image & salary details 
 11. inactive user login check
 12. permission management by admin
  
permission showing logic:
  1. after login set array of permission_lists of this user in session
  2. check button before showing it
